a minimum of 30 minutes per week.

6
00:00:23,022 --> 00:00:24,441
I have 90 more seconds.

7
00:00:24,524 --> 00:00:26,234
The judge ain't here. I am.

8
00:00:27,819 --> 00:00:30,530
Let's see what you're so hot for
without an Internet connection.

9
00:00:31,531 --> 00:00:32,574
BRIE: Bees.

10
00:00:33,325 --> 00:00:34,451
I like bees.

11
00:00:44,211 --> 00:00:46,546
(ALL GRUNTING)

12
00:00:48,298 --> 00:00:50,007
Thea, your back foot's sliding out.

13
00:00:50,092 --> 00:00:51,176
No, it's not!

14
00:00:51,676 --> 00:00:53,220
(GRUNTING)

15
00:00:54,221 --> 00:00:56,389
Just because you can't see me,
doesn't mean I'm not there.

16
00:00:56,473 --> 00:00:59,309
You gotta sense my presence,
even when I'm not in your eye-line.

17
00:00:59,392 --> 00:01:02,895
What advice would you
give to me? Humor me.

18
00:01:02,979 --> 00:01:04,314
Getting tired,
you're dropping your shoulder

19
00:01:04,397 --> 00:01:05,607
and you're opening yourself up.

20
00:01:05,690 --> 00:01:08,193
(BOTH GRUNTING)

21
00:01:14,991 --> 00:01:19,079
{\an8}So you took your morning run from
six miles, to what? Maybe two?

22
00:01:19,662 --> 00:01:22,540
{\an8}(GRUNTS) Yeah, well, taking care of
a toddler is a marathon in itself.

23
00:01:22,624 --> 00:01:24,334
{\an8}Right, but when you
sacrifice your endurance,

24
00:01:24,417 --> 00:01:27,504
{\an8}you're losing steam too early
in our sessions. Let's go again.

25
00:01:27,629 --> 00:01:28,921
{\an8}I'll pass.

26
00:01:29,005 --> 00:01:31,674
{\an8}I keep on running out of excuses
for all my new bruises.

27
00:01:31,758 --> 00:01:34,093
{\an8}And they're from you, not bad guys.

28
00:01:34,552 --> 00:01:37,013
{\an8}The streets have gone quiet since
we took Darhk off the board.

29
00:01:37,096 --> 00:01:39,891
{\an8}His organization hasn't been.
HIVE is still out there.

30
00:01:40,099 --> 00:01:41,976
{\an8}Yeah. And when they rear their head,
we'll take care of them,

31
00:01:42,059 --> 00:01:43,186
{\an8}but we have to celebrate our victories.

32
00:01:43,270 --> 00:01:45,438
{\an8}If we don't, we forget
what we're fighting for.

33
00:01:45,605 --> 00:01:47,274
{\an8}-(SIGHS)
-What's wrong?

34
00:01:47,565 --> 00:01:49,609
{\an8}Alex has a new job interview.

35
00:01:50,277 --> 00:01:51,694
{\an8}With Ruvé Darhk.

36
00:01:51,778 --> 00:01:52,820
{\an8}What?

37
00:01:52,904 --> 00:01:55,907
{\an8}She's looking for a new chief of staff
for the April 6th election.

38
00:01:55,990 --> 00:01:57,159
{\an8}Oh, still don't know see
why you just can't

39
00:01:57,242 --> 00:01:58,535
{\an8}put yourself back in the race, Oliver.

40
00:01:58,618 --> 00:02:02,205
{\an8}You know, voters, they hate flip-flopping
and that would be a pretty big one.

41
00:02:02,289 --> 00:02:05,708
{\an8}I can't let him work for the wife
of the prince of darkness.

42
00:02:05,792 --> 00:02:07,502
{\an8}And what if he got a better offer?

43
00:02:07,627 --> 00:02:09,045
{\an8}Are you gonna run for mayor?

44
00:02:09,129 --> 00:02:10,297
{\an8}Palmer Tech.

45
00:02:10,755 --> 00:02:12,715
{\an8}They're hiring
a new head of public relations.

46
00:02:13,007 --> 00:02:14,008
{\an8}Oh.

47
00:02:14,717 --> 00:02:17,970
{\an8}I just heard that from someone.

48
00:02:18,930 --> 00:02:21,224
{\an8}Laurel, she's not Voldemort.

49
00:02:21,808 --> 00:02:23,059
{\an8}And I'm fine.

50
00:02:23,351 --> 00:02:26,354
{\an8}That's a good idea.
You should tell Alex to talk to Felicity.

51
00:02:26,979 --> 00:02:28,148
{\an8}Mmm-hmm.

52
00:02:28,856 --> 00:02:30,692
{\an8}-What?
-Nothing. It's just...

53
00:02:31,693 --> 00:02:33,945
{\an8}What, it's shocking that you know
who Voldemort is.

54
00:02:34,279 --> 00:02:35,905
{\an8}Well, I mean,
I'm not immune to pop culture.

55
00:02:35,988 --> 00:02:37,532
{\an8}I read a few of the <i>Harry Potter</i> books.

56
00:02:37,615 --> 00:02:40,327
{\an8}Really? I was gonna bet Thea
that you just saw the movies.

57
00:02:41,453 --> 00:02:42,662
{\an8}There were movies?

58
00:02:48,710 --> 00:02:50,670
