{\an8}(SNEEZING)

76
00:03:46,518 --> 00:03:48,728
{\an8}Honestly, I think of this as a bargain.

77
00:03:48,895 --> 00:03:50,688
{\an8}Except we're not starting
a computer revolution here.

78
00:03:50,772 --> 00:03:52,565
{\an8}We're trying to repair spinal injuries.

79
00:03:52,940 --> 00:03:57,445
{\an8}The new estimate of spinal injuries
per year are at 12,000 people.

80
00:03:58,154 --> 00:04:01,574
{\an8}Unless everyone's a billionaire,
walking again is a luxury item.

81
00:04:01,699 --> 00:04:03,159
{\an8}Sounds like something
Mr. Dennis would say.

82
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:04,452
{\an8}He already has.

83
00:04:04,536 --> 00:04:06,746
{\an8}He's called a board meeting
to discuss how many zeroes

84
00:04:06,829 --> 00:04:08,290
{\an8}he can add to
the end of that price point.

85
00:04:08,540 --> 00:04:11,167
{\an8}(SNEEZES) Anything I can do to help you?

86
00:04:11,251 --> 00:04:12,710
{\an8}No, you can't do anything
with that cold. Go home,

87
00:04:12,794 --> 00:04:14,337
{\an8}get some rest.
Get some chicken noodle soup.

88
00:04:14,421 --> 00:04:16,005
{\an8}You sound like my mother.

89
00:04:16,088 --> 00:04:20,134
{\an8}Yeah, I'm sure if she was here, she'd tell
you to listen to my favorite girl.

90
00:04:20,718 --> 00:04:21,761
{\an8}Hi, honey.

91
00:04:21,844 --> 00:04:26,098
{\an8}Fine, but only because my cold medication
is starting to make me see double.

92
00:04:26,182 --> 00:04:27,809
{\an8}-Aw...
-Help. Help me, help...

93
00:04:27,892 --> 00:04:30,562
{\an8}Did you hear that?
