94
00:04:30,645 --> 00:04:31,896
{\an8}I don't think that's what he said.

95
00:04:32,021 --> 00:04:33,398
{\an8}(CHUCKLES) I think he did.

96
00:04:33,565 --> 00:04:34,774
{\an8}What can I help you with, Mom?

97
00:04:34,857 --> 00:04:38,069
{\an8}Well, my beautiful baby girl.
I am here to rescue you.

98
00:04:38,152 --> 00:04:39,612
-Oh.
-After the...

99
00:04:40,363 --> 00:04:41,448
(SIGHS)

100
00:04:41,573 --> 00:04:44,534
B-R-E-A-C-K-U-P,

101
00:04:44,784 --> 00:04:47,620
you could use some
regular socialization so...

102
00:04:48,204 --> 00:04:49,789
How about leisurely lunch?

103
00:04:49,872 --> 00:04:50,998
Oh, my God. I don't know what's worse.

104
00:04:51,082 --> 00:04:53,751
The fact that you just spelled out
breakup or that you misspelled it.

105
00:04:53,835 --> 00:04:54,919
-Huh?
-Yeah.

106
00:04:55,252 --> 00:04:56,921
-No.
-No, Mom. I'm fine.

107
00:04:57,004 --> 00:04:58,172
I have a lot of work to do.

108
00:04:58,255 --> 00:04:59,799
No. Just a quick one. Sweetie...

109
00:05:00,132 --> 00:05:02,051
Sorry. Is this a bad time?

110
00:05:02,134 --> 00:05:04,721
You people are like Tribbles today.
What's up? Everything okay with...

111
00:05:04,804 --> 00:05:06,473
-Oliver?
-I was gonna say your night job.

112
00:05:06,556 --> 00:05:07,932
You know, that thing that you do at night.

113
00:05:08,015 --> 00:05:09,601
{\an8}Yeah, no, that... That's fine.

114
00:05:09,684 --> 00:05:11,894
{\an8}Ollie is... Is fine too.

115
00:05:12,103 --> 00:05:14,063
{\an8}It's actually about Alex.

116
00:05:14,146 --> 00:05:16,023
{\an8}Um, he's no longer working
on the campaign so I was...

117
00:05:16,107 --> 00:05:17,734
-(PHONE RINGING)
-Oh, my God, it's Mr. Dennis.

118
00:05:18,610 --> 00:05:19,736
I have a board meeting.

119
00:05:19,819 --> 00:05:22,530
You know what? He's a jerk. He can wait.

120
00:05:24,281 --> 00:05:25,658
What did you wanna ask me about Alex?

121
00:05:28,995 --> 00:05:31,247
(CHUCKLES) You know,
usually someone buys me dinner

122
00:05:31,331 --> 00:05:32,915
before we start breaking out the cuffs.

123
00:05:33,124 --> 00:05:34,459
(LAUGHS)

124
