I thought you just lost your magic,
but your charm seems to be waning as well.

125
00:05:41,340 --> 00:05:42,592
How the hell did you get in here?

126
00:05:42,675 --> 00:05:44,343
(CHUCKLES) I used to be Ra's Al Ghul.

127
00:05:44,427 --> 00:05:46,554
Yes. This, I know. What I'm less clear of?

128
00:05:46,929 --> 00:05:49,849
Is why my resources haven't been deployed
to get me out of here.

129
00:05:49,932 --> 00:05:51,518
Well, that's what I'm here to explain.

130
00:05:52,685 --> 00:05:56,063
Although my time in here might be
limitless, Malcolm, my patience isn't.

131
00:05:56,147 --> 00:05:57,231
That's cute.

132
00:05:58,065 --> 00:06:00,568
As I was saying, I've been
in touch with your resources

133
00:06:00,652 --> 00:06:03,780
and they don't seem to have any
particular love left for you, Damien.

134
00:06:03,863 --> 00:06:06,616
Something to do with hocus and pocus

135
00:06:06,699 --> 00:06:08,951
and killing fellow members
when you get miffed.

136
00:06:10,077 --> 00:06:12,830
HIVE is moving forward with Genesis
but not with you.

137
00:06:13,372 --> 00:06:15,917
They like you here, out of trouble.

138
00:06:16,459 --> 00:06:18,920
But they do wish you
the best of luck with your trial.

139
00:06:19,045 --> 00:06:20,422
(GRUNTS)

140
00:06:21,881 --> 00:06:24,091
(CHUCKLES) Don't be embarrassed.

141
00:06:24,509 --> 00:06:27,261
Performance issues are common
for men of your age.

142
00:06:40,107 --> 00:06:41,233
(GRUNTS)

143
00:06:41,901 --> 00:06:43,736
Whoa, you really do have eyes
in the back of your head.

144
00:06:44,320 --> 00:06:45,404
I thought you had work to do.

145
00:06:45,488 --> 00:06:46,573
I realized it could wait.

146
00:06:47,532 --> 00:06:49,784
You've been pushing us pretty hard
and I know why.

147
00:06:50,577 --> 00:06:52,662
Oliver, it's okay to miss Felicity.

148
00:06:52,912 --> 00:06:55,998
I... I appreciate what you're doing but
I don't think that you're the...

149
00:06:56,082 --> 00:06:57,374
Person to help you through it?

150
00:06:58,250 --> 00:06:59,376
Why?

151
00:07:00,127 --> 00:07:01,921
-Because of what we used to have?
-Yeah.

152
00:07:02,755 --> 00:07:04,340
But maybe, it just gave me
a little insight.

153
00:07:04,423 --> 00:07:08,595
Well, I mean, in fairness, I did
wreck what we had too, so...

154
00:07:08,803 --> 00:07:10,304
In your defense, you were

155
00:07:10,888 --> 00:07:13,891
missing and presumed dead for five years,
but that's not what I mean.

156
00:07:15,142 --> 00:07:17,061
I know how passionately you love

157
00:07:17,144 --> 00:07:19,939
and how much it hurts
once that love goes away.

158
00:07:21,148 --> 00:07:22,442
You know, between...

159
00:07:24,026 --> 00:07:27,697
Merlyn, Slade Wilson and Ra's al Ghul,
I thought that I'd be a little...

160
00:07:28,698 --> 00:07:30,241
Tougher than this by now.

161
00:07:30,450 --> 00:07:31,743
That's a different type of pain.

162
00:07:33,077 --> 00:07:34,912
And this takes longer to heal.

163
00:07:35,412 --> 00:07:36,623
But I'm here for you.

164
00:07:37,790 --> 00:07:38,875
Thank you.

165
00:07:43,838 --> 00:07:45,214
You're not late, Phil.

166
00:07:45,297 --> 00:07:47,509
We're still waiting on Ms. Smoak.

167
00:07:51,387 --> 00:07:53,848
-(GRUNTING)
-Are you all right?

168
00:07:54,974 --> 00:07:58,102
Phil? Phil? Phil!

169
00:08:00,396 --> 00:08:01,814
I'm calling 911.

170
00:08:01,898 --> 00:08:04,025
-(YELLING)
-I can't get a signal!

171
00:08:06,986 --> 00:08:09,321
You'll have to excuse my tiny friends.

172
00:08:09,822 --> 00:08:13,618
Their bee-havior can be
appalling sometimes.

173
00:08:16,037 --> 00:08:18,372
But it's a necessary evil.

174
00:08:18,455 --> 00:08:21,250
You see, I needed your full attention.

175
00:08:21,333 --> 00:08:22,544
What the hell do you want?

176
00:08:22,794 --> 00:08:24,295
Straight to the point.

177
00:08:24,504 --> 00:08:25,672
I like that.

178
00:08:26,213 --> 00:08:29,258
Your CEO has miraculously
recovered from paralysis,

179
00:08:29,341 --> 00:08:32,887
thanks to an implantable
bio-stimulant microchip.

180
00:08:33,387 --> 00:08:37,850
Hand one over and I'll "bee" on my way.

181
00:08:37,934 --> 00:08:39,185
There's only one prototype...

182
00:08:39,268 --> 00:08:40,603
The one inside Felicity Smoak.

183
00:08:41,813 --> 00:08:45,191
So, what's a girl gotta to do
to get on her calendar?

184
00:08:46,275 --> 00:08:47,944
I can talk to Alex if you want,

185
00:08:48,027 --> 00:08:49,779
but I can't promise a job
he'll be excited about.

186
00:08:49,862 --> 00:08:52,615
Probably best to keep him away
from a super-villain's wife

187
00:08:52,699 --> 00:08:54,450
THEA: (CHUCKLES) Yep,
you're right about that.

188
00:08:56,536 --> 00:08:57,704
BRIE: <i>Hello out there.</i>

189
00:08:58,162 --> 00:08:59,371
What the hell?

190
00:08:59,496 --> 00:09:01,332
<i>I am looking for Felicity Smoak.</i>

191
00:09:01,457 --> 00:09:05,795
<i>Because it would be swell if we could
chat about a certain implantable bio-chip.</i>

192
00:09:06,546 --> 00:09:10,049
<i>I'm sure your board would
bee-ally appreciate it.</i>

193
00:09:16,222 --> 00:09:17,599
Brie Larvan.

194
00:09:17,682 --> 00:09:19,809
-You know this wackadoodle?
-I had a run-in with her last year.

195
00:09:19,892 --> 00:09:22,186
If this Brie Larvan is coming for you,
we need to get you out of here

196
00:09:22,269 --> 00:09:23,730
No, no, no.
No, I don't think she knew who I was.

197
00:09:23,813 --> 00:09:24,981
She's after something else.

198
00:09:25,064 --> 00:09:26,232
She said something about an implant.

199
00:09:26,315 --> 00:09:28,693
A bio-stimulant microchip.
There's only one working prototype.

200
00:09:28,776 --> 00:09:30,402
-Where is it?
-In the base of my spine.

201
00:09:30,486 --> 00:09:32,822
Which brings me back to, we need
to get you the hell out of here

202
00:09:32,905 --> 00:09:34,406
But we have to get everyone out of here.

203
00:09:34,490 --> 00:09:35,575
I can't even get a signal

204
00:09:35,658 --> 00:09:37,284
FELICITY: She's jammed all communications.

205
00:09:37,785 --> 00:09:38,870
Oh, my God...

206
