But how is this going
to help us save Oliver?

476
00:21:36,462 --> 00:21:37,879
Just give him a full Mariah Carey

477
00:21:37,963 --> 00:21:40,549
and it should disrupt whatever connection
the bees are operating on.

478
00:21:40,632 --> 00:21:42,301
All right, man. You sure about this?

479
00:21:42,468 --> 00:21:44,970
(GRUNTS) We don't have time to be sure.

480
00:21:46,179 --> 00:21:47,306
Curtis, do it!

481
00:21:48,390 --> 00:21:50,517
Three, two, one...

482
00:21:51,477 --> 00:21:53,144
(SCREAMING)

483
00:21:53,269 --> 00:21:54,355
(GRUNTS)

484
00:21:58,692 --> 00:22:00,026
(BEEPING)

485
00:22:07,826 --> 00:22:09,786
(PANTS)

486
00:22:11,705 --> 00:22:14,708
That was awesome.

487
00:22:18,128 --> 00:22:19,170
(SIGHS)

488
00:22:20,171 --> 00:22:21,590
You son of a bitch.

489
00:22:21,923 --> 00:22:24,175
(BOTH GRUNTING)

490
00:22:40,191 --> 00:22:42,318
My victory is inevitable, Mr. Queen.

491
00:22:42,861 --> 00:22:47,198
Just think, all of this power came
from the life essence of one man.

492
00:22:47,449 --> 00:22:51,828
Imagine what I will become when dozens
of lives are sacrificed in my name.

493
00:22:52,037 --> 00:22:54,080
(BREATHES HEAVILY)
You'll become a monster.

494
00:22:54,540 --> 00:22:55,707
-No.
-(COUGHS)

495
00:22:55,916 --> 00:22:58,419
A god. Let me show you.

496
00:23:10,055 --> 00:23:11,264
(GRUNTS)

497
00:23:12,474 --> 00:23:14,726
No, I need more. (PANTING)

498
00:23:17,228 --> 00:23:18,564
-You get 'em?
-Yeah.

499
00:23:19,022 --> 00:23:21,149
They were in Curtis' office.
Right where you said they'd be.

500
00:23:21,232 --> 00:23:22,859
-Uh, no pun unintended.
-(DONNA GASPS)

501
00:23:23,569 --> 00:23:26,697
This is like that thing from that, uh,
that Jodie Foster movie.

502
00:23:26,780 --> 00:23:28,198
Yeah. Uh, <i>Panic Room?</i>

503
00:23:28,281 --> 00:23:29,616
It's actually more like a lair.
Decommissioned.

504
00:23:29,700 --> 00:23:30,909
But if we can get
the board members in there,

505
00:23:30,992 --> 00:23:32,285
they can escape through a secret exit.

506
00:23:32,368 --> 00:23:33,495
Secret exit?

507
00:23:33,954 --> 00:23:36,582
Um, don't you think you should
have thought of that, like,

508
00:23:37,248 --> 00:23:38,542
I don't know, 15 minutes ago?

509
00:23:38,625 --> 00:23:40,919
Oh, I'm sorry,
I was busy trying not to die.

510
00:23:41,002 --> 00:23:42,504
And you were talking, talking, talking.

511
00:23:42,588 --> 00:23:44,214
Well, you don't open up to me, hon.

512
00:23:44,297 --> 00:23:46,467
I have to force your feelings
out of you sometimes like...

513
00:23:47,718 --> 00:23:49,553
-Like a pistachio.
-THEA: Okay, Smoaks.

514
00:23:49,636 --> 00:23:50,804
We gotta go. Come on.

515
00:23:51,262 --> 00:23:52,598
(BEES BUZZING)

516
00:23:53,557 --> 00:23:54,891
-Felicity...
-Mom.

517
00:23:55,100 --> 00:23:57,603
No, I meant... Felicity!

518
00:23:58,103 --> 00:24:00,564
(SCREAMING)

519
00:24:02,691 --> 00:24:04,275
-Okay, we're moving...
-(BREATHES HEAVILY)

520
00:24:04,359 --> 00:24:05,527
I know. Hold on to something.

521
00:24:05,611 --> 00:24:06,945
-What? Why?
-Why?

522
00:24:07,028 --> 00:24:10,448
This elevator, it only stops at the
sub-level and we need to stop it at...

523
00:24:10,657 --> 00:24:12,158
(ALL GASP)

524
00:24:12,826 --> 00:24:15,161
-Conference room floor.
-(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

525
00:24:16,121 --> 00:24:18,499
Oh... I think we missed our stop.

526
00:24:18,582 --> 00:24:21,710
No, this is right. Like I said,
the elevator doesn't stop at this level.

527
00:24:21,793 --> 00:24:24,337
What? Um, honey, I think
this is a concrete wall.

528
00:24:24,420 --> 00:24:26,381
Yeah, and these are explosive devices.

529
00:24:26,464 --> 00:24:28,424
Actually, they're autonomous
communication devices.

530
00:24:28,509 --> 00:24:30,385
I'm just really hoping that
Curtis hasn't figured out

531
00:24:30,468 --> 00:24:32,220
how to stop them from exploding.

532
00:24:32,303 --> 00:24:34,139
-Oh...
-DONNA: Be careful.

533
00:24:36,725 --> 00:24:38,226
Oh, my God. They're gonna blow.

534
00:24:38,309 --> 00:24:39,435
-Okay.
-Oh, God!

535
00:24:46,317 --> 00:24:48,278
(BOARD MEMBERS COUGHING)

536
00:24:48,486 --> 00:24:51,031
Okay, who wants to go on
a secret elevator right now to the, um...

537
00:24:51,114 --> 00:24:53,033
-Panic room.
-Yeah, the panic room.

538
00:24:53,324 --> 00:24:55,118
-FELICITY: Come on.
-(THEA COUGHING)

539
00:24:55,201 --> 00:24:56,327
Come on.

540
00:24:57,328 --> 00:24:58,705
Trying to escape the hive?

541
00:25:02,668 --> 00:25:03,752
Keep them safe.

542
00:25:03,835 --> 00:25:05,546
Huh? What?

543
00:25:11,593 --> 00:25:13,595
Beautiful creatures, my bees.

544
00:25:13,679 --> 00:25:15,722
-They obey you?
-Neural implants.

545
00:25:15,806 --> 00:25:17,933
You used to control them
the old-fashioned way.

546
00:25:19,517 --> 00:25:20,602
How did you know that?

547
00:25:21,978 --> 00:25:23,146
Lucky guess, I guess.

548
00:25:23,521 --> 00:25:27,233
So why bees? Why not an obsession
with flying squirrels?

549
00:25:27,442 --> 00:25:30,904
Squirrels aren't dying off
at a rate of 30% per year.

550
00:25:31,404 --> 00:25:34,616
And nobody cares,
but bees are essential to life.

551
00:25:34,700 --> 00:25:38,662
We're all connected.
The world is one giant honeycomb.

552
00:25:38,954 --> 00:25:40,538
Kumbaya might have
a little more credibility

553
00:25:40,622 --> 00:25:42,165
if you weren't threatening
people's lives.

554
00:25:42,373 --> 00:25:43,458
What, you mean like this?

555
00:25:44,500 --> 00:25:47,963
I am running out of patience,
and your friend is running out of time.

556
00:25:48,046 --> 00:25:49,297
Now give me the damn...

557
00:25:50,882 --> 00:25:51,883
(GRUNTS)

558
00:25:54,552 --> 00:25:55,887
That was embarrassing.

559
00:25:59,515 --> 00:26:01,517
I have a tumor on my L4 vertebrae.

560
00:26:02,560 --> 00:26:04,605
The tricky little guy's wrapped
around my spinal cord.

561
00:26:06,607 --> 00:26:08,900
The only way to cut it out
involves a surgery

562
00:26:08,984 --> 00:26:12,445
that will leave me paralyzed
from the waist down.

563
00:26:13,655 --> 00:26:15,741
All the bees in the world couldn't
get a cripple to walk.

564
00:26:18,201 --> 00:26:20,411
And then I read about your miracle chip.

565
00:26:20,996 --> 00:26:23,164
Of course... (CHUCKLES)
I couldn't afford it.

566
00:26:23,289 --> 00:26:24,499
Maybe if you asked nicely...

567
00:26:24,582 --> 00:26:28,419
I want the microchip specs or your friend
relives my favorite scene from <i>My Girl.</i>

568
00:26:28,503 --> 00:26:33,549
Okay, honey, we all have a sad sob story,
but killing people doesn't fix anything.

569
00:26:33,884 --> 00:26:36,386
The blueprints are on a remote hard drive
in Curtis Holt's lab.

570
00:26:38,346 --> 00:26:39,555
You are a smart girl.

571
00:26:46,354 --> 00:26:50,651
Elastic nanotubes, ultrasonic motors,
piezo ceramic elements...

572
00:26:50,734 --> 00:26:52,318
I mean, this bee's got everything.

573
00:26:52,485 --> 00:26:53,987
(CLEARS THROAT) That was inside me?

574
00:26:54,070 --> 00:26:56,531
Well, that and thousands of its
microscopic larvae.

575
00:26:56,907 --> 00:26:59,117
Don't worry. Should pass in a few days.

576
00:26:59,575 --> 00:27:00,661
Can't wait.

577
00:27:00,994 --> 00:27:02,537
Donna and the others made it out.

578
00:27:02,620 --> 00:27:04,247
-Thea and Felicity?
-They're still inside.

579
00:27:04,790 --> 00:27:06,499
Well, at least now we know
this stops the bees.

580
00:27:06,582 --> 00:27:08,877
I wish it was that simple, but now
that we've played that card,

581
00:27:08,960 --> 00:27:10,336
they've undoubtedly adapted to it.

582
00:27:10,962 --> 00:27:14,090
But we just beat a group of robot bees
using a superhero doohickey,

583
00:27:14,174 --> 00:27:15,801
if that's not high-five worthy,
I don't know what is.

584
00:27:15,884 --> 00:27:18,636
Curtis. Now is not
the time for high fives.

585
00:27:19,637 --> 00:27:21,765
Sorry. I, you know,
just got excited and...

586
00:27:22,307 --> 00:27:24,142
You know, you gotta celebrate the wins
when they come.

587
00:27:24,392 --> 00:27:25,435
What?

588
00:27:26,561 --> 00:27:28,563
Thea and Felicity are still trapped
inside Palmer Tech

589
00:27:28,646 --> 00:27:29,898
with who knows how many more bees.

590
00:27:29,981 --> 00:27:31,149
-We're not winning.
-Oliver...

591
00:27:31,232 --> 00:27:33,276
So, if you're gonna be down here,
if you're gonna be with us

592
00:27:33,359 --> 00:27:36,446
then you need to understand the totality
of what it is you're signing up for.

593
00:27:36,529 --> 00:27:39,783
If we do not do our jobs perfectly,
then people die!

594
00:27:39,866 --> 00:27:42,953
And not just strangers but friends,
family and loved ones!

595
00:27:43,036 --> 00:27:45,455
So think about that every time
you crack a joke

596
00:27:45,538 --> 00:27:47,833
-or make light of what it is that we do!
-Hey!

597
00:27:49,667 --> 00:27:51,336
Can I talk to you for a second?

598
00:27:57,592 --> 00:27:59,928
Any puppies you wanna kick
while you're at it?

599
00:28:00,011 --> 00:28:03,014
Bags of kittens that you wanna
throw down the river?

600
00:28:03,098 --> 00:28:04,307
He needed to hear that.

601
00:28:04,390 --> 00:28:06,017
Nobody needs to hear that, Oliver.

602
00:28:07,060 --> 00:28:08,937
I know you're hurting, but you can't
take it out on Curtis.

603
00:28:09,020 --> 00:28:11,940
I'm not taking it out on Curtis
I just need him to see.

604
00:28:12,482 --> 00:28:14,692
-See what?
-That this is not a good life.

605
00:28:15,861 --> 00:28:17,528
I walked away from it.

606
00:28:18,113 --> 00:28:19,322
And I was happy.

607
00:28:20,698 --> 00:28:22,367
For the first time in

608
00:28:23,744 --> 00:28:24,870
eight years,

609
00:28:26,079 --> 00:28:27,247
I was content.

610
00:28:28,123 --> 00:28:30,708
-So why did you come back?
-I came back because of Felicity.

611
00:28:31,752 --> 00:28:33,711
She convinced me that
we could do this job,

612
00:28:33,795 --> 00:28:36,214
that we could save the city, and not...

613
00:28:36,714 --> 00:28:38,466
Surrender to the darkness but...

614
00:28:41,302 --> 00:28:43,847
I don't... I don't think that we can.

615
00:28:44,347 --> 00:28:48,518
You're only saying that right now because
you're in 10 different kinds of pain.

616
00:28:49,227 --> 00:28:51,604
But the harsh truth is that Felicity,

617
00:28:52,438 --> 00:28:54,900
she broke up with you
because of your choices.

618
00:28:55,566 --> 00:28:58,737
Because the lies that you told.
You, Oliver. Not the Green Arrow.

619
00:28:58,820 --> 00:28:59,863
I know.

620
00:29:02,407 --> 00:29:06,036
It just doesn't seem fair that I can save
a city, and not save my relationship.

621
00:29:06,119 --> 00:29:08,329
Oliver, life's not fair.

622
00:29:08,413 --> 00:29:09,622
(SIGHS)

623
00:29:09,748 --> 00:29:12,125
Whether you're in Star City or Ivy Town.

624
00:29:13,501 --> 00:29:14,585
But you're right.

625
00:29:15,586 --> 00:29:17,756
You can save this city.
You do it every night.

626
00:29:19,257 --> 00:29:20,926
You're a beacon of hope to people.

627
00:29:23,178 --> 00:29:26,097
I just wish that you would try and use
some of that hope for yourself.

628
00:29:39,610 --> 00:29:40,695
Oh, hi, fellas.

629
00:29:40,779 --> 00:29:43,698
You know, I usually frown upon walk-ins
but how can I help you?

630
00:29:43,949 --> 00:29:47,327
No guards are coming to save you
this time, Darhk. We made sure of it.

631
00:29:47,410 --> 00:29:50,288
Good. Because then he'll only
has to kill two of you.

632
00:29:51,122 --> 00:29:53,291
(BOTH GRUNTING)

633
00:29:55,335 --> 00:29:57,212
I now you're probably asking yourself,

634
00:29:57,295 --> 00:29:59,422
"What the hell just happened?"

635
00:29:59,965 --> 00:30:02,383
It turns out your friend,
my new friend, Mr. Amar,

636
00:30:02,467 --> 00:30:05,386
has a soft spot for his
only surviving relative.

637
00:30:05,470 --> 00:30:07,305
A grandmother in Monument Point.

638
00:30:08,014 --> 00:30:11,767
It is amazing what people will tell you
with a few phone calls and a kind voice.

639
00:30:12,310 --> 00:30:13,478
Anyway, uh...

640
00:30:13,812 --> 00:30:15,230
Are they dead? Are they dead?

641
00:30:15,313 --> 00:30:17,482
No! I had this wonderful speech about how

642
00:30:17,565 --> 00:30:20,318
I was gonna kill your grandmother
had you not killed them...

643
00:30:21,111 --> 00:30:22,863
Never mind. On to other matters.

644
00:30:24,322 --> 00:30:27,993
You many now call your organization
and have that other message delivered.

645
00:30:31,496 --> 00:30:33,081
(LAUGHING)

646
00:30:36,376 --> 00:30:37,752
I thought we were locked out.

647
00:30:38,086 --> 00:30:40,463
Well, we're gonna have to see
if I haven't lost my touch.

648
00:30:40,546 --> 00:30:43,008
And I have to see if my mom
and the board members made it to safety.

649
00:30:43,341 --> 00:30:45,593
You really shouldn't have given
Brie what she wanted.

650
00:30:45,676 --> 00:30:48,471
I'm sick of people being put
in vulnerable positions.

651
00:30:48,554 --> 00:30:50,891
Yeah, well, now there's nothing
stopping her from bringing those

652
00:30:50,974 --> 00:30:52,225
bee things back on us.

653
00:30:52,308 --> 00:30:55,937
Well, at the very least it buys us,
the team... Your team, time.

654
00:30:57,438 --> 00:30:58,689
Ollie's gonna be fine.

655
00:30:59,815 --> 00:31:00,901
He always is.

656
00:31:01,067 --> 00:31:02,944
Well, unfortunately,
in Oliver's case, "he always is"

657
00:31:03,028 --> 00:31:04,737
isn't an accurate predictive metric.

658
00:31:05,530 --> 00:31:08,658
I'm sorry. I'm just sick of worrying.
I'm sick of the violence...

659
00:31:08,741 --> 00:31:11,244
Hey, so am I, okay? Of course I am.

660
00:31:12,203 --> 00:31:14,747
But we put up with it, we push past it.

661
00:31:15,331 --> 00:31:17,876
Because what we do is important, okay?

662
00:31:17,959 --> 00:31:19,502
We have to be that beacon of hope.

663
00:31:21,004 --> 00:31:22,213
Nobody else is.

664
00:31:22,297 --> 00:31:23,464
You're the beacon of hope.

665
00:31:24,174 --> 00:31:26,634
I quit the team because I couldn't
stand to work with Oliver, but...

666
00:31:27,760 --> 00:31:30,889
But now that I'm out, I look at life from
a different perspective.

667
00:31:30,972 --> 00:31:32,140
I mean, look around you.

668
00:31:33,183 --> 00:31:34,893
Thea, we're in a <i>Die Hard</i> movie with bees.

669
00:31:35,685 --> 00:31:38,980
Maybe I'm meant for great things, maybe
I'm not but whatever it is, it's not this.

670
00:31:40,731 --> 00:31:42,984
I'm sorry. I'm not coming back.

671
00:31:46,446 --> 00:31:47,530
Curtis...

672
00:31:48,656 --> 00:31:51,952
You know, I'm beginning to see why
you and Felicity didn't work out.

673
00:31:53,036 --> 00:31:54,245
Probably deserve that.

674
00:31:54,370 --> 00:31:57,332
Look, I'm all for hugs and learning
but, like you said, there's still danger.

675
00:31:57,916 --> 00:31:58,917
Yeah.

676
00:31:59,084 --> 00:32:00,543
And you are a very scary man.

677
00:32:01,252 --> 00:32:02,462
DIGGLE: Any luck with the bees?

678
00:32:03,421 --> 00:32:04,505
Curtis is doing his best.

679
00:32:04,630 --> 00:32:05,756
Thanks, Laurel.

680
00:32:06,091 --> 00:32:08,009
Now that I've been able to actually
examine the bee,

681
00:32:08,093 --> 00:32:09,802
I've deciphered their upgrade protocol.

682
00:32:10,303 --> 00:32:12,263
The next time they adapt,
I can upload a virus

683
00:32:12,347 --> 00:32:13,723
that will disperse into the entire hive.

684
00:32:13,974 --> 00:32:15,433
Like what they did in
<i>Independence Day</i>, right?

685
00:32:16,767 --> 00:32:18,103
What? I can't watch movies too?

686
00:32:18,186 --> 00:32:19,270
So what's the plan?

687
00:32:19,938 --> 00:32:22,983
I rigged an arrow with
a computer virus payload.

688
00:32:23,066 --> 00:32:24,775
Shoot it near one of Bee Arthur's minions,

689
00:32:24,859 --> 00:32:27,612
the virus will transmit to the rest
of the colony and we're done.

690
00:32:29,280 --> 00:32:30,490
That's nice work.

691
00:32:31,116 --> 00:32:32,700
(WHIMPERS) Uh...

692
00:32:33,534 --> 00:32:35,286
Wait until it works before
you congratulate me.

693
00:32:35,703 --> 00:32:37,956
(GASPS) I'm in. I mean, I'm out.
I mean, I have Internet.

694
00:32:39,124 --> 00:32:41,042
-Mom and the board members, they're okay.
-What about us?

695
00:32:41,126 --> 00:32:42,293
I'm working on overriding the bees,

696
00:32:42,377 --> 00:32:43,711
the ones that are outside
guarding the building

697
00:32:43,794 --> 00:32:44,837
BRIE: Don't bother.

698
00:32:48,716 --> 00:32:51,136
These blueprints will be useful.
Thanks for those.

699
00:32:51,344 --> 00:32:53,972
You have what you want.
So go build it yourself!

700
00:32:54,055 --> 00:32:55,306
I think we're confused.

701
00:32:55,931 --> 00:32:59,435
To get the schematics, I had to tip-toe
through Palmer Tech's computer network.

702
00:32:59,978 --> 00:33:03,564
And I saw some
very familiar computer code.

703
00:33:04,607 --> 00:33:06,985
You never forget the hacker
who sent you to prison.

704
00:33:08,569 --> 00:33:09,612
Hi...

705
00:33:12,865 --> 00:33:13,908
SPARTAN: We're clear.

706
00:33:13,992 --> 00:33:15,326
BLACK CANARY: At least
there's no signs of the bees.

707
00:33:15,410 --> 00:33:16,661
(BEES BUZZING)

708
00:33:17,953 --> 00:33:19,164
(SCREAMING)

709
00:33:20,748 --> 00:33:21,749
Go!

710
00:33:24,919 --> 00:33:26,462
(GASPING)

711
00:33:26,587 --> 00:33:28,089
(GUN FIRING)

712
00:33:28,173 --> 00:33:30,008
Looks like your green friend
didn't forget about you.

713
00:33:34,470 --> 00:33:35,721
Never will.

714
00:33:37,182 --> 00:33:38,766
-Hey, are you hurt?
-I'm okay.

715
00:33:38,849 --> 00:33:39,975
Hey! Behind you!

716
00:33:40,226 --> 00:33:41,311
(FELICITY GASPS)

717
00:33:42,770 --> 00:33:44,647
There you go. Team Arrow,

718
00:33:44,730 --> 00:33:46,649
which I am now a member of, pinch me,

719
00:33:46,732 --> 00:33:50,195
I need a few more minutes to hack this
latest firewall the bees adapted.

720
00:33:54,865 --> 00:33:56,284
I thought you were a better shot.

721
00:33:58,369 --> 00:33:59,912
(THEA GRUNTING)

722
00:34:01,706 --> 00:34:03,083
(GROWLING)

723
00:34:05,710 --> 00:34:07,628
(GRUNTING)

724
00:34:14,552 --> 00:34:16,429
Come on. Come on, come on,
come on, come on.

725
00:34:16,971 --> 00:34:18,139
Got you.

726
00:34:18,306 --> 00:34:19,849
(BEE BUZZING)

727
00:34:20,350 --> 00:34:22,518
(GASPING)

728
00:34:37,867 --> 00:34:39,577
(GRUNTING)

729
00:34:59,139 --> 00:35:00,765
(SCREAMING)

730
00:35:04,560 --> 00:35:05,686
(YELPS)

731
00:35:07,522 --> 00:35:08,648
(GASPING)

732
00:35:15,113 --> 00:35:16,197
Ew!

733
00:35:16,739 --> 00:35:18,908
(GRUNTS) Don't worry, I won't tell
anyone you screamed.

734
00:35:19,159 --> 00:35:20,368
-Oh, right.
-(GRUNTS)

735
00:35:26,624 --> 00:35:27,708
(GRUNTS)

736
00:35:29,001 --> 00:35:30,211
-Thank you.
-(SIGHS)

737
00:35:30,295 --> 00:35:33,131
You never, never have to thank me.

738
00:35:36,259 --> 00:35:37,302
(GRUNTS)

739
00:35:37,385 --> 00:35:39,929
If I can't walk, you can't live.

740
00:35:45,351 --> 00:35:48,729
Who should I kill first? A or "bee?"

741
00:35:51,149 --> 00:35:52,983
-(BEES BUZZING)
-CURTIS: <i>Guess who's back in control?</i>

742
00:35:53,067 --> 00:35:55,486
It's me, Curtis. In case you guys
don't recognize my voice yet.

743
00:35:56,654 --> 00:35:58,823
No. No, no. (GRUNTS)

744
00:35:59,449 --> 00:36:00,991
(BRIE STRUGGLING)

745
00:36:04,662 --> 00:36:07,957
(CHUCKLES) Lay down, bee-yotch.

746
00:36:08,499 --> 00:36:09,625
(CHUCKLES)

747
00:36:10,710 --> 00:36:11,836
Too on the nose?

748
00:36:21,846 --> 00:36:22,847
(CHUCKLES)

749
00:36:23,055 --> 00:36:24,682
The bee came alive and, well,

750
00:36:24,765 --> 00:36:27,227
things got a little out of hand.
But don't worry, it's dead now.

751
00:36:27,685 --> 00:36:29,854
You did good, Curtis. And I'm...

752
00:36:30,938 --> 00:36:32,773
I'm sorry if I made you feel differently.

753
00:36:34,192 --> 00:36:36,319
Thanks, GA. (CHUCKLES)
You mind if I call you GA?

754
00:36:36,944 --> 00:36:39,071
All right, yeah, I'll just stick
to Oliver then. (CHUCKLES)

755
00:36:39,154 --> 00:36:41,949
Or Mr. Queen. What about Larvan?
What's gonna happen to her?

756
00:36:42,325 --> 00:36:44,910
She's at Starling General.
Overdosed on toxins from the bees

757
00:36:44,994 --> 00:36:46,454
and is in some sort of a coma.

758
00:36:46,537 --> 00:36:49,039
More importantly, she's no longer
holding a dozen innocent hostages.

759
00:36:50,124 --> 00:36:52,502
That's both comforting and horrifying
at the same time.

760
00:36:52,627 --> 00:36:53,878
Welcome to our world.

761
00:36:54,337 --> 00:36:55,380
Hey...

762
00:36:55,630 --> 00:36:56,964
-(SIGHS)
-Is everything all right?

763
00:36:57,507 --> 00:37:00,050
Yeah, you know, I should probably
just head home.

764
00:37:00,426 --> 00:37:02,512
You know, learning that
you are, you know, you

765
00:37:02,595 --> 00:37:04,972
and the murderous bees,
and this coma news...

766
00:37:05,055 --> 00:37:06,641
It's just a lot to digest.

767
00:37:06,724 --> 00:37:09,018
Plus the IV you guys gave me
is starting to wear off.

768
00:37:09,101 --> 00:37:11,646
Well, you are always welcome here, Curtis.

769
00:37:11,729 --> 00:37:14,899
Just keep the property damage to
a minimum next time. (CHUCKLES)

770
00:37:15,733 --> 00:37:16,776
Okay.

771
00:37:18,569 --> 00:37:19,904
-What's the exit?
-Right there.

772
00:37:19,987 --> 00:37:21,071
Oh, yeah. (CLEARS THROAT)

773
00:37:24,409 --> 00:37:26,911
Hey. Nice apology.

774
00:37:26,994 --> 00:37:29,955
Well, I'm just trying to
be a beacon of hope.

775
00:37:30,831 --> 00:37:34,209
And like you said, save a little bit
of that hope for myself.

776
00:37:39,257 --> 00:37:41,175
(SOFTLY) Taiana. Hey, hey.

777
00:37:41,551 --> 00:37:43,844
All right. All right. Hey, Jesus.

778
00:37:43,928 --> 00:37:45,471
Come on, come on.

779
00:37:45,888 --> 00:37:48,558
Oh, thank God. Hey, Taiana, wake up. Hey.

780
00:37:48,808 --> 00:37:49,975
Oliver...

781
00:37:50,476 --> 00:37:52,019
It's okay. You're okay...

782
00:37:52,102 --> 00:37:53,313
-No.
-It's all right.

783
00:37:53,396 --> 00:37:54,772
No, Reiter...

784
00:37:55,523 --> 00:37:56,649
He's gone.

785
00:37:57,692 --> 00:37:59,944
He must be in the tunnels
searching for his idol.

786
00:38:00,445 --> 00:38:01,696
We can't let him find it.

787
00:38:01,779 --> 00:38:03,489
If he's in the tunnels,
searching for his idol,

788
00:38:03,948 --> 00:38:05,408
that means he's not going to the prison.

789
00:38:06,451 --> 00:38:08,411
This our chance to save your friends.

790
00:38:08,536 --> 00:38:09,829
And what of Reiter's men?

791
00:38:10,538 --> 00:38:11,789
They are still up there.

792
00:38:12,832 --> 00:38:14,500
(PANTING)

793
00:38:16,877 --> 00:38:18,629
That's why we're gonna
kill all of them first.

794
00:38:23,968 --> 00:38:25,094
(DOOR OPENS)

795
00:38:26,971 --> 00:38:29,474
I don't suppose it's too late
to reheat that soup?

796
00:38:31,016 --> 00:38:33,894
Where have you been? You bolted
out of here like a crazy person.

797
00:38:33,978 --> 00:38:36,981
Like some kind of a superhero
off to save the day.

798
00:38:37,106 --> 00:38:39,942
I was chasing some silly fantasy
that I can help the police.

799
00:38:40,776 --> 00:38:44,489
It was scary and thrilling and
dangerous and... Did I mention scary?

800
00:38:45,114 --> 00:38:48,075
The... The point is, is that I saw enough

801
00:38:48,158 --> 00:38:51,371
to know that this is where I belong.

802
00:38:52,497 --> 00:38:54,164
At home, with you.

803
00:38:55,375 --> 00:38:56,834
So no more disappearing acts?

804
00:38:57,627 --> 00:38:59,587
I promise. (COUGHING)

805
00:38:59,795 --> 00:39:01,714
(SIGHS) Let's get you some of that soup.

806
00:39:05,092 --> 00:39:06,176
Terrific. (CHUCKLES)

807
00:39:06,969 --> 00:39:10,097
(GRUNTS) Maybe I should burn
some incense in here or something.

808
00:39:11,181 --> 00:39:13,559
Probably a very good idea.

809
00:39:13,643 --> 00:39:16,854
Remind me to never wear
black and yellow ever again.

810
00:39:16,937 --> 00:39:18,022
(CHUCKLES)

811
00:39:18,689 --> 00:39:19,940
Wait, where'd your mom go?

812
00:39:20,107 --> 00:39:21,526
Oh, Captain Lance drove her home.

813
00:39:21,651 --> 00:39:24,028
Yeah, that is something I'll never
be able to wrap my brain around.

814
00:39:24,153 --> 00:39:26,113
-(CHUCKLES) Kinda cute.
-(CHUCKLES)

815
00:39:27,948 --> 00:39:29,116
Don't you miss this?

816
00:39:30,200 --> 00:39:34,038
I mean, I... I know you said that you
wanted to get away from it all but...

817
00:39:35,373 --> 00:39:36,416
How could you?

818
00:39:37,207 --> 00:39:38,333
What do you mean?

819
00:39:38,418 --> 00:39:41,045
This. The, the thrill of this. The rush.

820
00:39:41,128 --> 00:39:43,631
I mean, we just took down
a bad "bee-yotch" tonight.

821
00:39:43,714 --> 00:39:44,799
(CHUCKLES)

822
00:39:44,882 --> 00:39:46,258
It doesn't get any better than this.

823
00:39:46,592 --> 00:39:47,843
I was never in it for that.

824
00:39:49,554 --> 00:39:50,638
Not ever.

825
00:39:52,432 --> 00:39:53,724
I wanted to make a difference.

826
00:39:54,684 --> 00:39:57,019
Be part of that
beacon of hope you speak of.

827
00:39:57,645 --> 00:39:58,813
So come back.

828
00:39:59,814 --> 00:40:00,940
Rejoin the team.

829
00:40:02,232 --> 00:40:03,651
I think I figured out another way.

830
00:40:05,069 --> 00:40:09,239
It's actually, that insane bee lady
who gave me the idea. Ironically.

831
00:40:09,949 --> 00:40:11,075
(SIGHS)

832
00:40:11,617 --> 00:40:12,827
To remake this company.

833
00:40:14,078 --> 00:40:15,663
To use the technology that
helped me walk again

834
00:40:15,746 --> 00:40:16,872
to make people's lives better.

835
00:40:18,082 --> 00:40:21,461
To make Palmer Tech into a beacon of hope.

836
00:40:27,467 --> 00:40:31,887
Our mutual friends in HIVE have abandoned
our other mutual friend Mr. Darhk.

837
00:40:33,097 --> 00:40:34,389
But he reached out to me.

838
00:40:35,516 --> 00:40:36,767
Told me about you.

839
00:40:37,727 --> 00:40:40,688
He said you were his ace in the hole.

840
00:40:40,771 --> 00:40:42,022
(CHUCKLES)

841
00:40:42,565 --> 00:40:43,899
Is that what you'd like me to call you?

842
00:40:45,943 --> 00:40:48,278
Or do you prefer Mr. Diggle?

